\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 36. R. pulcher} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 336 (1753). Perennial 20-60 cm. Plant often papillose. Basal leaves small, fleshy, about twice as long as wide, usually panduriform, cordate at the base. Panicle open; branches usually divaricate, flexuous, often entangled or arcuate; whorls all remote and subtended by a leaf. Pedicels thick, shorter than to as long as the valves; fruits scarcely deciduous. Valves thick, coarsely foveolate-rugose, variable in outline; at least 1 valve with a large rugose or verrucose tubercle.{\i  Mainly ruderal. S. & W. Europe, extending to Hungary and N. Romania.} Al Az Bl Br Bu Co Cr Ga Ge Gr Hb He Hs Hu It Ju Lu Rm Rs(K) Sa Si Tu [Au He].
