\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b a}) Subsp.{\b  pulcher} : Basal leaves usually panduriform. Branches angular-flexuous, often forming an intricate mass. Valves 4-5 mm, narrowly ovate or oblong, with lingulate apex; 1 or 2 meshes of venation on each side of the tubercle; teeth 1-2 mm, 4 on each margin. 2n = 20.{\i  Throughout the range of the species}.
\par

