\par

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b c}) Subsp.{\b  woodsii} (De Not.) Arcangeli, {\i Comp. Fl. Ital.} 585 (1882) (subsp.{\i  divaricatus} (L.) Murb.): Basal leaves seldom panduriform. Branches arcuate-divaricate. Valves 4-5 mm, suborbicular or ovate-triangular, broadly acuminate at the apex; usually 3 meshes of venation on each side of the tubercle; teeth 0·5-1 mm, up to 8 on each margin. 2n = 20.{\i  S. Europe}.
\par

