\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 37. R. obtusifolius} L.,{\i  Sp. Pl}. 335 (1753). Perennial 60-120 cm. Basal leaves large, twice as long as wide, thin, obtuse or subacute, cordate at the base; petiole slightly longer than the lamina. Panicle open; branches arcuate; whorls mostly remote, the lower ones subtended by a leaf. Pedicels slender, up to 2½ times as long as the valves; fruits readily deciduous. Valves 3-6 × 2-3 mm.{\i  Europe, except the extreme north and south.} All except Cr Is Sb Si, but only as an alien in Az Fe and perhaps Rs(N).
