\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b a}) Subsp.{\b  obtusifolius} (subsp.{\i  agrestis} (Fries) Celak.): Leaves papillose beneath. Valves ovate or ovate-triangular, with several distinct, often long teeth, obtuse; 1 valve with a tubercle. 2n = 40.{\i  Cultivated ground, pastures and waste places. Native in W. Europe, and widely naturalized elsewhere}.
\par

