\par

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b c}) Subsp.{\b  transiens} (Simonkai) Rech. fil.,{\i  Beih. Bot. Centr.}{\b  49}({\b 2}): 52 (1932): Leaves somewhat papillose beneath. Valves ovate to narrowly triangular, with a few teeth near the base, obtuse to subacute; all valves with tubercles. 2n = 40.{\i  Mainly ruderal. C. Europe, Balkan peninsula, S. Scandinavia; locally naturalized elsewhere}.
\par

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b d}) Subsp.{\b  silvestris} Celak.,{\i  Prodr. Fl. Böhm.} 159 (1871) (subsp.{\i  sylvestris }(Wallr.) Rech.,{\i  R. sylvestris} Wallr.): Leaves smooth beneath. Valves narrowly triangular or lingulate, entire or with a few short or indistinct teeth near the base, subacute; all valves with tubercles. 2n = 40.{\i  Riversides, woodland margins, and as a ruderal. Europe from Italy and Sweden eastwards; occasionally naturalized elsewhere}.
